               </para>
			         </problem.body>
         </problem>
			      <approach version="1">
				        <answer.exercise>
               <answer.exercise.block>
                  <answer.exercise.block.body>
					                <para>
                        <para.body>False!</para.body>
                     </para>
				              </answer.exercise.block.body>
               </answer.exercise.block>
            </answer.exercise>
				        <solution>
               <solution.body>
					             <para>
                     <para.body>The rank of a system of linear equations is the number of leading <math>
                           <latex>1</latex>
                        </math>’s in the RREF of the non-augmented coefficient matrix of the system. This number is always less than or equal to the number of variables in the system.</para.body>
                  </para>
					             <para>
                     <para.body>Therefore the statement in question is false.</para.body>
                  </para>
				           </solution.body>
            </solution>
			      </approach>
		    </part.exercise>
		
